*/Problem- 203.Remove Linked List Element
Platform-Leetcode
Difficulty-Easy
Frequency-1ms
Approach(Basic iterative method)-
First remove all nodes from the beginning whose value equals val.
Traverse the linked list using a pointer curr.
If curr.next.val == val, skip that node by changing links.
Otherwise, move curr forward.
Return the updated head of the list.
Solution-*/

class Solution {
    public ListNode removeElements(ListNode head, int val) {
        while(head != null && head.val == val){
            head = head.next;
        }
        ListNode curr=head;
        while(curr != null &&curr.next!=null){
            if(curr.next.val==val){
                curr.next=curr.next.next;
            }
            else{
            curr=curr.next;
        }}
        return head;
    }
}
